abstract.p: Defense Department confirms deaths of 11 American service members in Iraq, bringing total to 3,269 (S)

block.p: The Department of Defense has identified 3,269 American service members who have died since the start of the Iraq war. It confirmed the deaths of the following Americans this week:
BILLITER, Gregory J., 36, Chief Petty Officer, Navy; Villa Hills, Ky.; Explosive Ordnance Disposal Unit 11.
BURGE, Jerry C., 39, Staff Sgt., Army; Carriere, Miss.; First Cavalry Division.
CANTRELL, Joseph H. IV, 23, Cpl., Army; Ashland, Ky.; First Cavalry Division.
DALLAM, Ryan S., 24, Specialist, Army; Norman, Okla.; First Infantry Division.
FREEMAN, Walter Jr., 20, Pfc., Army; Lancaster, Calif.; Second Infantry Division.
GIBSON, Derek A. 20, Pfc., Army; Eustis, Fla.; Second Infantry Division.
HALL, Curtis R., 24, Petty Officer Second Class, Navy; Burley, Idaho; Explosive Ordnance Disposal Unit 11.
LOPEZ RODRIGUEZ, Damian, Private, Army; Tucson; First Infantry Division.
McSWEEN, Joseph A., 26, Petty Officer First Class, Navy; Valdosta, Ga.; Explosive Ordnance Disposal Unit 11.
NEEL, Phillip I., 27, First Lt., Army; of Maryland; First Cavalry Division.
PALERMO, Anthony, 26, Capt., Army; Brockton, Mass.; First Infantry Division.
